{"word":"ἄρδω","slug":"ἄρδω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄρδω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to water</i>, and so,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>of men, <i>to water</i> cattle, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to drink</i>, <el>ἀρδόμενοι</el> h. <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of rivers, <i>to water</i> land, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>irrigare</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be watered</i>, of countries or crops, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to refresh, cherish</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>fovere</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}